reviewText: I have purchased this item in hopes of getting back in shape after having a baby and taking a 2-year hiatus from exercizing.  I just tried it and was very disappointed - while it started nice, the whole last third of the workout is way too hard for me (and I defy any TRUE beginner to fare better than me), to the point where I can't follow it at all.  Which significantly shortens an already short workout and is disappointing - I felt up for a few more exercises I actually could do, and instead I found myself struggling (and failing) to do the teasers.  The modifier hardly helps a true beginner with weak abs who is only looking to build them.I'm also guessing it will take me longer than a week or two to build up to the level where I can do the entire length as it needs to be done.  In the meantime, I get a supershort workout and a lot of frustration.Perhaps a great video for someone with already strong abs who's looking for more definition or simply a new routine to add variety, but not so great for someone like me.
summary: Not good for a true beginner

reviewText: I was really impressed with how Mari's thighs and glutes workout reshaped my butt, so I thought I would add this to my dvd collection. Well hello, abs! I'm in decent shape - I am in the military and did 96 sit ups in two minutes (only one guy beat me, I'm the only female in my unit). I didn't think this would be much of a challenge but I was sore for a few days after the workout.

reviewText: From all the Winsor DVD's this one is by far the most effective and my favorite.  This video is approximately 20 minute long and focuses solely on ab or the "core" muscles.  I have never had stronger and more defined abs!  I love my mid section now, because of this video.  I have been doing the Winsor pilates videos for about 4 months, and I've lost weight, toned my muscles, and have fun every time I excercise.
